    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In the context of buying a home, escrow refers to an account held by a lawyer or a third-party escrow agent where you'll temporarily hold funds until the closing of the sale. The escrow account is used to hold the purchase price and any closing costs until the title transfer is complete. This ensures that you'll have the funds available for payment when the transaction is finalized, and helps to prevent issues with non-payment. It's a common practice in Toronto and other parts of Canada.",
