      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's accurate. The escrow account is typically managed by a lawyer or a third-party escrow agent who oversees the funds and ensures that they're held securely until the closing date. In Toronto, a common escrow agent is a title company or a lawyer specializing in real estate transactions. They're responsible for collecting the funds, holding them in escrow, and distributing them according to the terms of the sale when the transaction is complete.",
